EMAIL NOTIFICATION SYSTEM
    A complete email notification system  was added to automatically alert users when their account  status changes.This sytem  handles  both approval  events and delivers branded ,HTML-formatted emails.

1.1.1  app/Mail/UserApprovalNotification.php

A new Mailable class responsible for configuring and dispatching account status emails.
    •Class: Extends Laravel's built-in 
    •Dependencies: Accepts two constructor arguments: the target 
    •View Binding: Binds both variables to the email view for dynamic rendering.

Key constructor Signature:
    public function __construct(public User $user, public string $status) {}

1.1.2  resources/views/emails/user_status.blade.php
    A new HTML email template providing a polished user-facing notification for account status changes.
    •Approval State: Renders an 'Account Approved' message with a direct login button when status = approved.
    •Disapproval State: Renders an 'Account Disapproved' message with support information when status = disapproved.
    •Dynamic Content: Dynamically injects the user's name and status from the Mailable class.
    •Design: Clean, professional HTML/CSS styling consistent with the application's branding.

1.2  Authentication Middleware
    1.2.1  app/Http/Middleware/Authenticate.php
    A custom authentication middleware class was created to override Laravel's default unauthenticated redirect behaviour for API consumers.
    •Purpose: Overrides the default 
    •API Safety: Returns a structured JSON error response instead of attempting an HTML redirect.
    •Behaviour: Ensures pure API applications receive machine-readable 401 responses on authentication failure.

Response format returned on failure:
HTTP 401 Unauthorized
{ "message": "Unauthenticated." }

2. Modified Files
The following existing files were updated as part of this release.

2.1  UserController.php
Path: Modules/Users/Controllers/UserController.php
Major refactoring was performed to integrate email notifications alongside all user status change operations.

2.1.1  Added Dependencies
Two new imports were added at the top of the controller:
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Mail;
use App\Mail\UserApprovalNotification;

2.1.2  approveUser()
•Refactored method structure and formatting for readability.
•Added model refresh (fresh()) after the status update to ensure the mail receives the latest data.
•Wrapped email dispatch in a try/catch block to prevent approval failures if mail delivery fails.
•Added Log::info on successful mail send and Log::error on failure.

Email dispatch pattern:
Mail::to($user->email)->send(new UserApprovalNotification($user, 'approved'));

2.1.3  disapproveUser()
•Identical email notification pattern applied for disapproval events.
•Passes 'disapproved' as the status string to trigger the correct email template branch.
•Includes the same try/catch guard and structured logging.

Email dispatch pattern:
Mail::to($user->email)->send(new UserApprovalNotification($user, 'disapproved'));

2.1.4  Bulk Action Methods
The following bulk methods were all updated with email notification logic:
•approveMultipleUsers()
•disapproveMultipleUsers()
•processMultipleApprovals()

Changes applied uniformly across all three methods:
    ◦Iterates through each processed user individually.
    ◦Sends the appropriate approval or disapproval email per user.
    ◦Wraps each individual mail send in its own try/catch to prevent a single failure from aborting the batch.
    ◦Logs success and error outcomes per user with structured context data.

2.2  Exception Handler
    Path: app/Exceptions/Handler.php
    The exception handler was updated to ensure all API error responses are consistently JSON-formatted.

2.2.1  render() Method
    •Updated to explicitly return a JSON response when the incoming request expects JSON.
    •Response includes the exception message and an appropriate HTTP status code.
    •Prevents unintended HTML error pages being returned to API consumers.

Example JSON error response:
{ "message": "Resource not found." }   // HTTP 404

2.2.2  unauthenticated() Override
    •Added a dedicated override for Laravel's AuthenticationException.
    •Always returns { "message": "Unauthenticated." } with a 401 status code.
    •Eliminates accidental redirect responses for API consumers.

2.2.3  Cache Error Handling
    •Retained existing specific handling for cache directory missing / permission errors.
    •No functional changes were made to this section.

2.3  App Bootstrap
    Path: bootstrap/app.php
    The application bootstrap file was modified to explicitly register the custom authentication middleware alias.

2.3.1  Middleware Alias Registration
    •Registered the 'auth' alias pointing to the new custom middleware class.
->withMiddleware(function (Middleware $middleware) {
    $middleware->alias([
        'auth' => \App\Http\Middleware\Authenticate::class,
    ]);
})

•Ensures the custom JSON-aware authentication middleware takes full precedence over Laravel's built-in redirect-based handler.
•This is the critical wiring step that activates the custom middleware across the entire application.


